<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFBFFA7F69EFE5539C9FDE0" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F69EFE5538A1FEB6" blockId="1.[164,779,460,513]" lastBlockId="1.[826,1441,198,342]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F69EFE553DC9FE01" box="[164,400,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Emended diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body high, head capsule well developed, durable, covered with a head shield. Post-cephalic body covered with valves. Antenna II relatively long (length of basal segment + exopod = about half body length), both branches three-segmented, antennal formula (4–7)– (1)–(3)/(1)–(1)–(3). Gut not convoluted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F500FE1639C9FDE0" blockId="1.[826,1441,399,512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F500FE16381CFE44" box="[826,1093,399,420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Unique antenna II (with lateral setae only on proximal segment of endopod) differentiates the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F242FE553945FE02" authorityName="Smirnov" authorityYear="1992" box="[1144,1308,460,482]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Prochydoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Prochydoridae</taxonomicName>
from any other family in the known orders of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F32DFE7339D5FDE0" box="[1303,1420,490,512]" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cladocera" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" rank="order">Cladocera</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFBFFA7F755FDAD388FFDAB" box="[367,1238,564,587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F755FDAD388FFDAB" blockId="1.[181,1424,564,800]" box="[367,1238,564,587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
KEY FOR DETERMINATION OF GENERA OF THE FAMILY 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F236FDAD388FFDAB" authority="SMIRNOV, 1992" authorityName="Smirnov" authorityYear="1992" box="[1036,1238,564,587]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Prochydoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">PROCHYDORIDAE</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFBFFA7F68FFDC439D6FCFF" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" type="key">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F68FFDC439C9FD6D" blockId="1.[181,1424,564,800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
1. Rostrum truncated in lateral view, ventral margin of valve armed with setae and denticles............................. ...................................................................................................................... 3. 
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F29EFDE339C9FD6D" bold="true" box="[1188,1424,634,653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F29EFDE33947FD6D" authority="Kotov, 2009" authorityName="Kotov" authorityYear="2009" box="[1188,1310,634,653]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Prochydoridae" genus="Palaeorak" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F29EFDE33947FD6D" bold="true" box="[1188,1310,634,653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Palaeorak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27F4030FFFBFFA7F31DFDE339C9FD6D" box="[1319,1424,634,653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F68FFD0E3FB0FD4A" blockId="1.[181,1424,564,800]" box="[181,1001,663,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">2. Rostrum pointed, ventral margin of valves without setae and/or denticles</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F68FFD2C39D6FD05" blockId="1.[181,1424,564,800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
3. Body very high, mandible attached to the valve at a distance from point of joint of head and valve, antenna II short ........................................................................................................ 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F256FD4B39D6FD05" authority="Smirnov, 1992" authorityName="ROTUNDUS SMIRNOV" authorityYear="1992" box="[1132,1423,722,741]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Prochydorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F256FD4B38B6FD05" box="[1132,1263,722,741]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Prochydorus</emphasis>
Smirnov, 1992
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFBFFA7F68FFD7639D6FCFF" blockId="1.[181,1424,564,800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
4. Body less high, mandible attached to the point of joint of head and valve, antenna II long................................. .................................................................................................................. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFBFFA7F2BDFC9539D6FCFF" authority="Smirnov, 1992" authorityName="MIRABILIS SMIRNOV" authorityYear="1992" box="[1159,1423,780,799]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Archeoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFBFFA7F2BDFC9538A8FCFF" box="[1159,1265,780,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Archeoxus</emphasis>
Smirnov, 1992
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
